        "is_accepted": true,
        "last_activity_date": 1542964084,
        "creation_date": 1542964084,
        "body": "<p>The <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/YAML\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">YAML format<\/a> supports UTF-8 by default, whereas <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/.properties\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">properties files<\/a> must be encoded and are read in the ISO-8859-1 encoding by definition. So any non-<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO/IEC_8859-1\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">ISO-8859-1<\/a> character is going to cause you issues unless you escape them in the .properties files.<\/p>\n\n<p>You escape the Unicode characters in properties files by using their hex code prefixed with \"\\u\". For example, \"ä\" would be encoded as <code>\\u00E4<\/code>, and the snowman, ☃, would be encoded as <code>\\u2603<\/code>. You can find the escape codes, for example, <a href=\"https://www.fileformat.info/info/unicode/\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">here<\/a>. <\/p>\n",
        "answer_id": 53443562,
        "question_id": 53442810
    }],
